Package: causalverse
Type: Package
Date: 2026-03-17
Title: The All-in-One Causal Inference Toolkit
Version: 1.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("Mike", "Nguyen", , "mikenguyen.contact@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-3432-8595"))
Maintainer: Mike Nguyen <mikenguyen.contact@gmail.com>
Description: A comprehensive, one-stop-shop toolkit for causal inference in R,
    the 'tidyverse' of causal analysis. Covers the full causal inference
    pipeline: randomized experiments (RCT, power analysis, attrition),
    quasi-experimental designs (DiD, staggered adoption, synthetic DID,
    synthetic controls, RD, IV), heterogeneous treatment effects (causal
    forests, BLP, GATES, Qini curves), mediation analysis, sensitivity
    analysis, panel data diagnostics, and publication-ready reporting.
    Provides 80+ utility functions, 13 in-depth vignettes, and
    seamless integration with leading causal inference packages.
